title: ''Πολύ καλό''
text: Το ψηλότερο κτίριο στο Μπανγιούλ. Τα σκαλιά είναι πάνω από 100 αλλά μπορείτε να τα ανεβείτε εύκολα και χαλαρά.Μόλις φτάσετε έχει ένα χώρο με κάποιες φωτογραφίες.Και φυσικά έχετε μια θέα της πόλης από ψηλά.

title: Tribute Arch That Offers a Great View of the City
text: We appreciated the tasteful tribute to the military coup July 1994 that offers views of Banjul.  This is the tallest structure in The Gambia and worth a visit.

title: Nice little museum at the top with a really good guide
text: We went up there to activate our kids a bit - we expected a nice view, which was indeed nice, but were happily surprised to find a very nice and competent guide at the top too, in a little museum. He could talk for hours about Gambian history.

title: Dictator
text: De boog geeft een mooi uitzicht op de kleine hoofdstad Banjul. Maar het schokkende museum erboven liet een zwarte periode uit de geschiedenis van gambia zien. Een van de voorgaande presidenten Jammeh had het land geregeerd als een harde dictator met moordeskaders. Vreselijk om te zien

title: Panoramic View of Banjul
text:
Located on the Banjul-Serrekunda highway into Banjul, is the commemorative arch built in 1996 Provisional Ruling Council overthrew the democratically elected Gambian government of President Sir Dawda Jawara.  A statue of the "unknown soldier" is set near the base of the arch:
Construction

At about 90 feet, the arch is one of the tallest structures in The Gambia. The building has three floors. Access to the upper floors can be made through a series of several marble spiral stairs.  Although there is an elevator it was not working.

Each floor provides a panorama of the city, with the top floor providing a view extending to the sea port of Banjul and the mangrove forests of Tanbi Wetland Complex. In the third level is a series of photos of  President Jawara.  Worth a climb if you are in reasonably good shape.

title: im Verfall
text:
Die Aussicht oben ist interessant, aber dann war es auch bereits.
Der Zustand ist erschreckend schlecht und dann gibt es zwar noch ein paar Räume zum anschauen, aber ohne Licht, sehr ungepflegt und alles im Zerfall.
Kein Besuch wert, wenn nicht die Aussicht wäre; kurzer Stop und dann ist genug; schade dass man es nicht ein wenig pflegt

title: Site de la ville
text: Avec les mosquées, c'est le seul lieu qui semble intéressant à  visiter sur Banjul. Entrée à 100 dalasis pour les étrangers, quelques marches puis une belle vue et surtout le lieu de regroupement des habitants. De près du port le taxi nous y a emmené aller retour avec 10 minutes d'attente environ pour 200 dalasis.

title: Interesting history and nice view
text: Nice view overlooking the city. It houses a small museum and shows the history of The Gambia. Bring a flashlight because it can be rather dark inside.

title: commemortivo
text: Sulla strada tra Banjul e Serrekunda si incrocia questo arco che commemora il colpo di stato. Con la sua quarantina di metri è una delle strutture più alte in zona e salendo si può vedere il panorama. C’è anche una statua al milite ignoto.

title: One if the only historic monuments
text: This is one of the only historic monuments in the country, it's an important place to visit. Up high you get to really see the city.

title: Kaprys byłego prezydenta
text: Duża budowla wybudowana przez i dla byłego prezydenta Gambii. Dobre miejsce do podziwiania stolicy najmniejszego państwa Afryki. Widoki niesamowite. W Srodku muzeum gdzie możemy zapoznać się z historią Gambii.

title: Arch22
text: Vi besökte monumentet som en del av en guidad rundresa i Banjul. Trappan upp var trång men utsikten uppifrån var fin. Dwt fanns en hiss, men den var trasig. Kändes som om monumentet skulle behöva rustas upp lite...

title: No es gran cosa
text: Este monumento conmemorativo está a la entrada de Banjul, cerca de la casa del presidente. Los coches pasan por debajo y su visita es muy corta.

title: Niente di Speciale.
text: Leggendo le guide pensi che sia qualcosa di importante da vedere, però quando ci arrivi, ti accorgi che non è niente di speciale. C'è la possibilità di salire sopra, ma non è che si vede tutto questo panorama.

title: Triumfbåge vid infarten till huvudstaden Banjul i Gambia.
text: Denna Triumfbåge byggdes för att fira minnet av militärkuppen den 22 Juli 1994. Monumentet är 36 meter högt och innehåller dessutom ett museum. Vägbanan ut och in till staden Banjul som ligger på en ö, passerar under Arch 22.

title: Stadtübersicht
text:
Wenn man sich einen Überblick über die Stadt verschaffen möchte, hier ist eine Möglichkeit. Im oberen Stockwerk befindet sich eine Ausstellung zur Geschichte des Landes. Man kann aus den halbrunden Balkon sehr schön über die Stadt, Parlament, Hafen und einer Moschee sehen.
Das Gebäude ist in einem erbärmlichen Zustand, Fahrstuhl defekt, daher für Behinderte  nicht wirklich ansehenswert, man muss Treppensteigen.
Am Fuße des Triumphbogens befindet sich eine Tribüne, hier wird man schnell Mitbringsel (Bonbons, Stifte u.ä.) los.
Nur wegen dem Bogen hinfahren lohnt nicht, im Rahmen einer Stadtrundfahrt nimmt man es eben mit.....

title: Eher unspektakulär
text: Nicht wirklich einen Besuch wert. Es sich anzuschauen, wenn man vorbei fährt oder geht, reicht eigentlich.

title: Mit dem Markt zusammen anschauen.
text:
Nette Sache , man kann über den Markt und die Stadt schauen. 
10 Minuten reichen hier für.
Also wenn man zum Markt will , einfach mit einplanen.
Raus aus dem Hotelzimmer. 
Rein ins Taxi.

title: Ein altes baufälliges Monument...mehr nicht
text: Wir haben es zwar nicht bestiegen, aber man soll angeblich von oben einen guten Blick über die Stadt haben.

title: Historisch interessant
text: De Arch op zich is niet zo heel indrukwekkend, gewoon een panorama op Banjul. Maar de bovenste verdieping biedt wel wat interessants: de slavenhistorie. Beelden, foto's en geschriften moeten ons duidelijk maken dat dit nooit meer mag gebeuren. Erg indrukwekkend.

title: Great view over Banjul
text: This monument is big and you can go up and see very good view and you can see over the Banjul city from here. Price to up is not much,  but view is nice. Defenetly worth of visit.

title: Great way to get a good view of the city
text: Walking up the stairs in the west-african heat may be a bit of an unexpected workout for some,but its worth visiting. Its not that tall a building, but given that there are no tall buildings in The Gambia, you can enjoy very good view of the city, take some great pics, enjoy the breeze and educate yourself in the small museum.

title: A rememberance of dictatorship
text: Not worth looking at it. A symbol of the formal dictatorship. Do not blow it up, just let nature do its work....

title: Waste of Money
text: I am aware that the arch is a commerative one but surely the money spent on its construction would have been better used elsewhere.

title: En triumfbåge med historia.
text:
Vi gjorde ett stopp på 15 min när vi passerade vilket alla gör då det är porten till Banjul. 
Trånga trappor att gå i, hissen är trasig. 
Fint att ta bilder över staden från toppen av bågen. 

Dåligt underhållen men sevärd.

title: A must when visiting banjul
text: Banjul is very known for this arch which is why you should see it if you’re ever in Banjul city. Not really that big of a deal but still.

title: Didn't go up
text: Didn't have a chance to go up but passed by a couple of times. Looks impressive from a distance and good land mark.

title: Its on the bank notes
text: You either drive under it or around pending which way you are going. Looks a bit run down from the street side but has a bloody history. Worth looking out for on your way to the ferry or exploring the sights and sounds of the capitol city

title: So much potential but run down
text: The arch is one of those must see monuments in The Gambia. Unfortunately it’s not been well looked after and maintained- the elevator doesn’t work and the stairway is really dark which is dangerous because it’s a winding, loopy staircase. When we reached the top after a long climb, I was expecting to see some sort of history or information on the monument but there wasn’t. For a small country, it’s still worth heading to for a look around.

title: En av få sevärdheter
text: Arch 22 är en av Banjuls få sevärdheter när det gäller arkitektur. Banjul är ingen stad man besöker för att se vackra byggnader...

title: Worn down monument
text:
Nothing much to see really... 
An worn down arch over a noisy road, steep stairs (no elevator).
View over ? Actually not that much!

title: an arch with a bad history
text:
When you are in Banjul do go for a visit to this Arch. It isn't that beautiful but it has a bloody history that will tell you about the dictator and the killings going on in front of the Arch.

On the other hand, going really on top of the rach gives you a great view over Banjul. There's also a small exposition above about the dictator and the Arch itself. 

Be advised that there is no elevator, so you have to climb by stairs!

title: Triumpfbogen in Afrika
text: Wenn man an der Küste von Sennegambia ist sollte man auf jeden Fall Banjul besuchen. Man wird am Eingang der

title: Very strange “museum”
text:
We payed the lady downstairs to go upstairs to have a visit, it was very dark and we had to turn on the lights as we walked along the upper floors. The stairs up there were very low, so be careful with your head if u are a bit taller (I’m 5.11 and had to duck a few times lol...)

Also be careful in one of the rooms there was a large square hole in the floor into the room below, with no balustrade around. 

Most of the exhibits seemed very old and dusty but it was interesting to read the informative boards of the Gambian history etc, it didn’t seem very looked after though which was a shame.
There was no one apart from me and my friend up there and no staff available. 
There had been a restaurant up there we were told but this had moved down to a small adjacent park which didn’t seem very busy.

Nice views from the upper floors though so interesting to see.
Luckily we had a torch with us though as when walking down the second set of stairs was in complete darkness ...

title: Sightseeing
text:
It could be seen whole city of Banjul with a bird watch. Also you can see Atlantic Ocean, mouth 👄 of River Gambia where you can cross by ferry boat. The width of the River Gambia between Banjul-Barra is approximately 7 kms, it takes you to pass the river 30 minutes. If you look backward you can see the delta of the river with MANGROVES SWAMP.
It is worth to climb.

title: Worth going for the view and history
text: This monument now celebrates the freedom of the Gambian people after the fall of the dictator Yahya Jammeh. The view from the top is good and there is a small exhibition (not really a museum) about the peaceful change of power. I don't think we paid to enter the Arch 22 but it would be worth a dollar or two.

title: Waanzinmonument : the Arch 22
text: De afgezette dictator Jammeh bouwde deze triomfboog ter meerdere eer en glorie van ...zichzelf. Hij was de enige die er met de auto onderdoor mocht, de rest van het volk moest omrijden. Tegenwoordig is er een kleine expositie in gevestigd over de -bij vlagen tragische- geschiedenis van Gambia. En je krijgt natuurlijk een mooi uitzicht over het kleine hoofdstadje.

title: ガンビア首都のシンボル
text: ガンビアの首都、バンジュールのシンボル的存在。上に登る階段があるが、訪問時は係がおらず登れなかった。ガンビアに来た記念に写真を撮りたい。

title: The entrance to Banjul city
text:
We had a private guided tour of the city and stopped here to learn about the recent history of the nation. The lift was out of action (I think it always is) and our guide suggested there were 100 steps up - maybe there are but it didn't seem that many once you started the climb - it's 114ft at the highest point and is supported by 8 huge columns. It is named July 22nd Arch in memory of the 1994 revolution.  

The museum is not worth the title - but the views are definitely worth the effort. From the new National Assembly building, down Independence Drive and right over to the ocean. It is possible to walk outside onto the bridge to have photographs un-obscured by the window glazing

title: Wasted potential
text: Feels like a tourist trap! Museum at the top was very disappointing. Perhaps the only good thing is the view you get from the top and it makes for a good picture. I would not go our of my way to visit this place. If its part of your city tour then thats ok. But if you're planning to just head out to the arch and make a day of it? DON'T!!!

title: Underneath The Arches
text: Unfortunately the tour we were on didn't stop here which was a shame. nevertheless passed right by it so got a reasonable view of it but no time to go up.

title: Worth the climb!
text: For a meagre 50 dalasi (less than £1, depending on the exchange rate!), Arch 22 provides a great view of Banjul and the Atlantic Ocean. A slight climb to the top gives an opportunity for some great panoramic shots, and the chance to see the city’s Parliamentary building, Independence Drive and dwellings. With it being such a cheap excursion, it’s a must-do when visiting Banjul.

title: Inte mycket att se
text: Stort monument för att vara i Gambia men egentligen rätt oansenligt. Inte värt en omväg för mog som europeisk turist.

title: Een kort bezoek waard
text: Vanaf boven op de arch mooi uitzicht . Je kan dit plannen samen met een bezoek aan het nationaal museum in Banjul.

title: Een beetje belachelijk.
text: De vorige president/dictator had beter een school of een kliniek gebouwd met het geld voor deze "arc de triomphe"

title: Zbyteczny łuk - STRATA CZASU
text: Łuk wybudowano nie wiadomo po co w biednej stolicy Gambii. To typowe "zadęcie" prezydenta. Łuk i obok niego podium do przyjmowania defilad. STRATA CZASU

title: Almost a must-see
text: If you travel around the town, you are almost bound to pass under this arch at some point. It is very much a local landmark. Built by the previous President, to commemorate his coming to power. One wonders if the new President is tempted to knock it down?

title: Worth the climb...
text: Yes...worth the climb to the top for a local panorama and some photos.  Best leave it to the last as you leave...rather than on the way in!

title: Nice view from the top
text: This is the no 1 landmark in Banjul built to commemorate the coup that brought the former dictator of Gambia Yayah Jammeh  to power. It is about the tallest structure in town. Climbing to the top is through circular staircase in the leg of the structure. The view from the top is nice and good for snapping pictures.

title: History
text: Great symbol of the country’s history. It literally takes minutes to appreciate it in all its glory so I wouldn’t make a day trip of it

title: Arch 22
text: A large arch celebrating independence . Basically the main entrance to Banjul City.the tallest structure in Banjul

title: Un arco en la carretera
text: En si no es muy magnificente... y si vas al centro antiguo de Banjul, casi seguro que pasarás por él. No vale la pena ir sólo para verlo.

title: Views from Banjul
text: I had the chance to visit the Arch 22 which was build to commemorate the 1994 revolution. The Arch houses various Gambian artifacts, and beautiful view of the capital.There is also a restaurant where you can eat and relax for the day.

title: nothing special, just an arch. Take some pictures, that is it
text:
Just an arch and you can take pictures. There were some seatings to the side across the judicial hall. 

Seriously, nothing exciting. 

If you are traveling, make sure to take your passport. There were several checkpoints and the police give you a hard time without one. 

Easily accessible.

title: A Tourist attraction easy to access
text: We stopped here on our visit to Banjul and it is easy to park nearby, there are eating and drinking facilities nearby so we stopped and took some photo's.  This is an easy tourist attraction to visit and it is also nice if you want to take your own picnic, plenty of space.

title: Arch
text: It is the only historical place what you can see in gambia so it is definetely good to visit this place and there is a nice view on the top of the arch as well.

title: L'OPERA
text: Costruito più di vent'anni fa per celebrare il colpo di stato alto una quarantina di metri è una delle pochissime attrazioni di Banjul quindi merita una visita

title: Gehört eigentlich abgerissen
text:
Da ich schon oft in Gambia war, habe ich auch den Arch 22 besucht. In den 90er Jahren war das eine "Sehenswürdigkeit", da nach dem Militärputsch 1994 erbaut. Ausblick von oben schön - aber das ist alles.
Nachdem nun der ehemalige "Präsident" das Land noch an den Rand eines Krieges gebracht hat, weil er nach den Neuwahlen im Dezember 2016 nicht abtreten wollte, gehört dieses "Denkmal" nun eigentlich abgerissen. Es ist ja ohnehin in einem schlechten Zustand und von einem Besuch würde ich eher abraten wegen Unfallgefahr (Liftschacht offen usw.)

title: Not what I expected!
text: The arch was built for the coup of President Jameyh, who was just voted out and forced to leave the country. They said there was a museum in the Arch. I don't know if I would call it that. It was an interesting building and had good views of the surrounding area. I think it is supposed to be free but there is usually some government worker at the entrance extorting money to gain entry.

title: Symbool van dictatuur
text: Wanstaltig gebouw, alleen gebouwd voor de megalomane gedachten van de vorige dictator, het beste wat ze kunnen doen is dat ding slopen

title: If in Banjul....it is there...
text:
Nothing monumental about any architecture in The Gambia and you will find some more interesting if empty modernistic office buildings dotted about. And this is no monumental arch of significance. Bland white concrete that has aged reasonably well.

Built post '94 to celebrate the military coup, which has now itself just ended in a mess of lost cash and economic tourist collapse, it has been largely ignored by the locals.  50 delasi get in and a hike of steps to the upper balcony, you do get a good photo view over the low town buildings and over to the dock cranes, over to the other side of the river on a clear day.  A bit of an ad hoc display of local art and history.

So an if in town option perhaps along with Albert Market and the football stadium.  Don't let your green car driver overcharge you on this one.

title: Must visit,The only architecture site in the Gambia
text: There is nice place to see, having excellent view to Banjul from its top balcony. Banjul is one store city, so it is a topmost point from where you can take nice shots and views to all city. Please, mind that elevators inside the column are usually broken, so you will need to climb up the spiral steps  to the top. For old people it can be hard task. There is a state museum inside with an information about The Gambia history. It is quite interesting/ I hope they will soon replace an exposition honoring their "great" doctor professor academic state savior etc. etc. former president mr. Jammeh, who was 20 years holding power robbing The Gambia so extensive, that after he was pushed out by Senegal forces in 2017, the State Treasury  appeared empty with last few millions of dollars transferred during  the last days of his presidency out of the country/ He even did not forget to take with him his luxury cars - god knows where he suppose to drive them in the Africa mostly without roads....

title: Like communist monuments
text: My guess is that they built this place for "once a year" parades. It look very communistic. But there is a nice small museum in the arch (entrance fee 50D = 1 Euro), you get a good view over Banjul from the top floor balcony. And there is a free toilet next to it. :)

title: Widok
text: Obiekt warty odwiedzenia jako klasyczny pomnik wystawiony sobie przez aktualną władzę. Jeszcze aktualną bo zmiana ma nastąpić za kilka dni. U góry wystawa wychwalająca jedynie słuszną linię Prezydenta Jammeha. Jedyny taki obiekt w tym regionie Afryki. Widok sympatyczny ;)

title: Arch 22
text: Very good and interesting place to visit, free of charge by the way and who minds giving a tip for the worker who sits by the door at the end of your visit !!

title: Näe koko Banjul
text: Kiipeä korkealle ja edessäsi aukeaa Banjul. Sisältä löytyy myös näyttely Gambian asioista. Meri ja joki yhdistyvät.

title: Gambia
text: Visited the arch, was OK lovely view stairs were quite dark and damp as a cleaner was washing them. Not somewhere you would spend a lot of time doing as not a lot at the top just for the view .

title: Quite interesting
text: Quite a hike up the steps to the top of the arch but a good museum display at the top. Great views of the area great photo stop

title: Disappointing
text:
This is a concrete building. The inside was complete empty. You can climb to the top of the building to have an overview of Banjul. The view isn't great (nothing particular to see in Banjul). Entrance was 50 dalasi or +/- 1 euro.
Visit takes 5 minutes

title: Joli point de vue sur l'ensemble de Banjul
text: Faites y une halte. Vous y découvrirez une très jolie vue sur Banjul, entourée d'eau. Quelques panneaux didactiques sont exposés, pour mieux comprendre l'histoire de ce pays.

title: nice place
text: not much to say but if you are in Banjul go and see the arch you can climb to the top for a good view

title: Prachtig monument
text: Prachtig monument in de Banjul. Alle trappen zijn we op gegaan. Wat een prachtig uitzicht ondanks de minimale bewolking.

title: Impressive
text: Built to commemorate the coup on 22/7/94 this huge impressive looking arch is well worth a visit if you are in the area. You can climb the steps to take pictures and you will also get far reaching views when you get to the top.

title: Newly constructed arch and building
text: Great to see this monument newly created in Gambia. We went to see this beautiful arch and building at its slender. The history is very interesting about the revaluation that took place. Lovely restaurant here with goof coffee and food. Parking area also at the venue.

title: Łuk Triumfalny w Banjul
text: Łuk Triumfalny , to 35-metrowa konstrukcja będąca symbolem miasta upamiętniającym bezkrwawy przewrót wojskowy, przeprowadzony w 1994r przez obecnego prezydenta Gambii Yahyę Jammeha. Jest ona również wieżą widokową, z której można zobaczyć panoramę miasta.

title: Niet te missen
text: Je kunt deze Arch niet missen als je vanuit Banjul met de Ferry naar de overkant vaart. Stukje geschiedenis.

title: Impressive looking arch
text: Impressive looking arch and a great photo opportunity. Commemorates the revolution and worth an hour of your time if  you get the chance

title: Great photos of Banjul
text: For many years it was am impressive arch to drive around and photo.  Now that you can climb up it is worth it for the views.  I have taken great city life photos without hassle.

title: Great view of Banjul
text: Just as you enter Banjul you have Arch 22 you can climb the steps to the top for great views over the Banjul

title: Small exhibition of juju medicine, good view
text: Good observation point, not too exciting. Some juju stuxff exhibited. Some tidiying up would be an ok pastime for the staff...

title: Als je dan toch in Banjul bent...
text:
Op excursie vanuit Kololi naar Banjul deden we met onze privé-gids c.q. taxi-chauffeur ook deze attractie aan. Je kunt deels met de lift naar boven en deels met de trap.

Ze noemen het een National Center For Arts And Culture, maar het museum stelt weinig voor. Een enkele aangeklede pop, enkele vitrines en wat foto's. Dan houdt het wel op. Wel leuk om gezien te hebben, maar ik vond het uitzicht leuker.

Voor de prijs hoef je het niet te laten. Laten we het daar maar op houden.

title: De mooie omgeving van boven bekijken doe je op Arch 22
text: De Arch 22 is het symbool van de machtsovername op 22 juli 1994 en is een boogvormige toegangspoort tot de hoofdstad Banjul. De Arch 22 is 35 meter hoog en het hoogste gebouw van Gambia. Je kan gratis naar boven lopen (een lift is er ook), hier heb je een prachtig uitzicht over de stad, de omgeving, de oceaan en de Gambiarivier. Op het verkeersplein voor de boog staat het standbeeld van de onbekende soldaat, die een baby draagt. Een bezoek aan Arch 22 en naar boven lopen is zeker de moeite waard.

title: It's big and impressive
text: Built to commemorate the 22 July date of Independence, it is a striking landmark if not that beautiful so I don't think I would make a special visit

title: Stelt niets voor.
text: Bespaar je de moeite, er is weinig te zien. De bevolking, dorpen, markten zijn allemaal véél interessanter.

title: Great view from the arch
text:
The view from the arch is great and the history displayed inside is really interesting. 

Not the best thing to do in the Gambia, but worth a visit.

title: Beautiful view
text: For 50 dalasi, you get a tour of the arch all the way to the top, and an excellent view of Banjul. However the museum at the top is extremely underwhelming (for lack of a better word). Half of the exhibit was pushed to the side and looked as if no one had been there in decades, but the view definitely made up for it.

title: Lovely day out in Banjul
text: Took my Gambian fiancé out to Banjul for the day to do a bit of shopping and R&R. taxi dropped us off next to the roundabout opposite Arch22. we had a lovely stroll around and spent some time looking at the nice green spaces. unfortunately they had scaffolding up painting Arch22, but it was still lovely to look out. TIP1. Keep you valuables' secured as my camera was stolen not from Banjul has to be said. and TIP2  make sure if entering Banjul you have ID on you especially if you are in a mixed race couple like me. But don't let that put you off please. was still a nice day out and if you go down some of the side streets in Banjul you will find bargains a lot cheaper than the tourist areas

title: An adventure on its own!
text:
You pay a ridiculously cheap entrance fee to the guardian (the staff at the hotel said it was free...) and here you go, up the arch.
It was under renovation so it's a bit rough, you go through sand and over wheelbarrows. The view is incredible, and you have several points of view depending you stand on one side of the arch or the other and there is different heights. The view of the old town was my favorite.

title: A privat monument of the president.
text:
its build by the president Jamme and its his privat monument over him self. Its just a building and nothing speciell to se or do there. And the building is not fitting the in the area and to the other buildings in the area.
I can't recommend any to make a special visit just for this.

title: Mouldy Sandwich
text:
Give this place a miss 
We were served a sandwich. The bread was blue & Mouldy, never felt well after that experience

title: serves no purpose
text: Recently renovated for the 50th anniversary of independence. It doesn't seem to serve any purpose. The lift was not working and I could not go up the stairs. There is a low priced café/restaurant near it that serves good food and drinks. It only allows government vehicles to pass through.

title: Arch 22
text: A nice place for a short visit if based in Banjul as we were. Wouldn't bother, however, driving a long distance just for this. Freshly renovated for Feb 18th 50th Anniversary of Independence from Great Britain. Pleasant inexpensive cafe at its foot.

title: Stupid bit of minor megalomania
text: A big arch to celebrate another African dictator's reign.  Unlike statues this might not be demolished when he is finally toppled but it is hard to see a purpose for such a pointless building

title: A lot of steps for not a lot of view
text: Greeted by two lovely ladies and set the task of counting the steps to the top I was quite disappointed by the rather tatty 'museum' exhibits on the way up and not really knowing what to expect was quite underwhelmed by the view(s) from the top. Stupidly expecting some sort of award for counting the steps I was then delighted with the cafe/bar next door which had recently changed hands. title: Barely worth the bother
text:
The grandiose Arch was built to commemorate the coming to power of H.E. Sheikh Professor Alhaji Dr. Yahya A.J.J. Jammeh,
President of the Republic of The Gambia and Commander-In-Chief of the Gambia Armed Forces.

In a country that has so much poverty, this structure seems both unnecessary and ill-advised.

Tourists can ascend the Arch in a lift. There is a moderately-interesting museum near the top and you certainly get some good views over the town and surrounding countryside. However, there are better museums (e.g. Katchikalli) and better roof-top views (e.g. Bakau Guest House), so I really can't recommend this.

Soft drinks can be bought from the cafe/ restaurant.the entry fee is nominal, and is much lower for Gambians. There are clean rest room facilities. Well worth a visit.

title: Great views
text: Cheap to go in and an option of lift or stairs to the top. Once at the top you have great views of Banjul and beyond. title: Life of Banjul from up above....
text:
We went to The Gambia in October 2012, and Arch 22 was one of the 1st sites we came across. You can park right beside the arch which, offers great convenience. The arch itself is not in great condition, and if we remember right, the entrance fee was 50 dalasi per person.
A museum is located half way up the arch, which displays Gambian culture before their  independence from Great Britain. Once up on the balcony of the arch, you now have a great view of the city of Banjul. if you have been to the city of Banjul, then you will know that the place is nothing special. But the views overlooking the city are great. Different stories are being told at every angle of your view, so take advantage because you won't have a better opportunity! At least the president has given the tourists a positive side of Banjul....

title: Neglected building but great view
text:
We took the short walk from our hotel and paid the fixed entrance price of 50 Dalasi. Inside the building is sadly neglected and poorly maintained but for the view alone it is certainly worth a visit. The lift may not function very well as we were encouraged to take the stairs and told by the attendant that 'excercise is good in the morning'! The spiral stairs are manageable and should not cause any concern for those of any age or ability. 

The exhibits are interesting and fill you in on the ancient tradition of 'Juju' culture in Gambia. Juju refers to the use of objects and other things to perform a form of witchcraft and a range of such objects are available to look at and learn about. These are a little dusty and poorly maintained but provide a fascinating insight into Juju culture in the Gambia. 

The view from the very top of the structure is best and worth continuing to the top for.

title: Cheap way to see Banjul from above

title: A good viewpoint for Banjul
text:
The Arch 22 is a good point to get an overview of the capital. The Arch itself and the exhibition on the top level are not really spectacular. You can - and I recomment to do so - take a lift up to the top level.
It was built in 1996 to mark the military coup on 22 July 1994.
The arch stands on the Banjul-Serrekunda highway. A statue of the unknown soldier can be seen near the base of the arch.

title: Arch22
text: It is not quite what it seems..It was built to celebrate the military takeover of the current president... there are two lifts, but only one works and you have to pay a fee. No one says you can walk up the arch for free until you get back down.  Up top it was disappointing.. the view was OK for long distance camera shots....but the top floor was a poorly equipped musuem and and a small tacky shop. The first floor was supposed to be a resturant at some time in the past , but was now shut.
